Well, i was in a severe badmood last couple of days. I hated seeing people, and it ruined my whole day really. So during this weekend, i kept my cell phone turned off so that nobody cant reach me, and i swear, it gave me a huge peace of mind. What im tryin to say is, that no life could be worth enough to just sit in the corner with your cell phones, communicate with people through text messages and chat apps, without really seeing their faces. People nowadays really need to re-learn how to speak to others, i guess. Grab some friends, go out, get lost in faraway places, experience it.
It's almost been 3 years already. I want to go back so pathetically bad 😭 #BeautifulMaryland #throwback

caption.text: Allahuakbar. Banyak hal yang terjadi 3 minggu belakangan ini, dari mulai ujian ujian sekolah yang pada akhirnya rontok satu per satu, terus ditunjuk sama depag buat jadi perwakilan garut dalam lomba MQK  ke 5 di tasik, ngerasa terhormat banget bisa kenal sama pak kasi, pak aom, dan bapak bapak depag lainnya yang ternyata pada gokil kebina bina, dapet pengalaman debat bahasa inggris dan dapet juara 2 se-jabar. Alhamdulillah. Terus oleh olehnya, saya dititipin penyakit sama Allah, sampe masuk rumah sakit dan dirawat seminggu, diambil darah tiap hari sampe akhirnya nangis juga hehehe. Anyway, dengan semua ini saya merasa sangat hidup, dengan begini artinya Allah masih memperhatikan saya, saya doakan semua, semoga sehat selalu dan bahagia selalu ya! Seperti keberadaan kipas angin sebagai sumber kehidupan dalam foto ini ♥ salam cinta buat fari sama rima, makasih udah sama sama dalam teriknya panas tasik dan sengitnya bertahan menghadapi bapak juri  yang itu tea gening hehe love yuaaahhh:)

Udah satu tahu ya? Hidup saya cukup aneh, pernah mimpi apa ya waktu dulu sampe tau tau bisa ngerasain hidup bareng sama dua angkatan yang berbeda? Meski begitu saya bersyukur, sangat. Mungkin waktunya singkat, namun banyak pelajaran baru yang saya dapatkan, juga teman baik. Terimakasih untuk satu tahun ini, telah mengizinkan saya hidup bersama kalian, bercanda dan menggila. Telah membiarkan saya menyatu, dan bergaul layaknya teman lama. It was an honor, and I am very grateful for that=)

caption.text: Ujian nasional, nempelin bet sekolah pake double tip -setelah sebelumnya dicabut paksa dari seragam yang udah mulai menguning atau kekecilan- kayaknya udah jadi kebiasaan 90% santri darul arqam. Termasuk saya. Tradisi yang bakal selalu dikenang sampe nanti tua. Foto ini saya ambil sesaat setelah ujian nasional berakhir, meskipun sebenernya pengen nangis teriak teriak gara gara soal fisika nya bikin sakit jantung, tapi euforia dari ujian nasional yang akhirnya selesai itu rasanya lebih dahsyat dari semua soal soal yang baru aja dikerjain. Pengen teriak sekeras kerasnya. Singkat cerita, akhirnya masa jadi SMA (santri madrasah aliyah) berakhir juga. 4 tahun ditambah mts 3 tahun jadinya 7 tahun. Bukan waktu yang singkat tentunya, banyak kenangan manis pahit, apalagi kejadian konyol nan culun. Ah, I am gonna miss you my Mahad Darul Arqam Muhammadiyah Garut♥♥

caption.text: "Saya nyantri loh, udah 5 tahun.. - tapi pelajaran agama islam terbaik yang pernah saya dapet, saya dapet di Amerika- negara berminoritas Muslim. "  this is my end-of-stay reflection, about all the things I've done throughout my journey in this so called land of Uncle Sam. Tonight, June 21st 2013 will temporarily be my last youth halaqah group at MCC -Muslim community center, MD- we had a nice dinner then followed up with a lecture about prophet Muhammad SAW. The imam told us a story about the death of prophet Muhammad SAW. And what will happens in a hereafter. He reminded us, about how the prophet Muhammad SAW. Is now still waiting for us to go with him to Jannah. The story, touched my heart to the point that I literary was weeping inside myself. I felt the whole embarrassment for the sins I've been building up and up in every single breath I take, and how generous Allah SWT is, to gives me this whole miracles and joyments in this life. Saya bersyukur dg sedalam dalamnya syukur ya Allah yang Maha Pengasih Maha Penyayang atas keluarga ini, keluarga Muslim Community Center yang membuat saya sadar akan segala nikmat yg pernah tersia2kan. Membuka mata saya akan keindahan islam yang sebenarnya. I never thought that I will ever find such thing in America, that I really am finding myself in this very night, about my identity as a Muslim. Asyhadu anlaa ilaaha illaAllah, wa asyhadu anna Muhammadarrosulullah. For this, I deeply, sincerely thanks America. Thanks for giving me this most precious gift I have ever had. Thanks Muslim Community Center. And most importantly, thanks Allah SWT for this whole scenarios of my extraordinary life that I believe You are the only one I must ever pray to. *the state of Maryland, United States of America. Ratu*

caption.text: Lol! I love this one, photo credit for Anna! :) site : National American History Museum, DC

Bismillah. Tapantri 1830 semua tentang kita akhirnya telah usai dan berlalu, meskipun saya dan fari memang tidak pernah hadir. Jika kalian mau tau bagaimana ini rasanya sangat ingin berlari kesana dan memeluk kalian semua saat ini juga, berlari membantai ribuan kilometer jarak yang membentang diantara kebersamaan kita! Kalian semua amatlah berharga bagi kami. Kalian adalah sumber kekuatan kami yang karena teramat besar sehingga mampu untuk mengantar kami ke negri ini, ribuan kilometer dari rumah kita bersama. 5 tahun tidak cukup bagi saya dan fari untuk kehilangan kalian begitu saja, namun Tuhan mempunyai rencana hidup yang lebih indah untuk kita semua.. kalian tahu, andai tiket pesawat itu gratis, kami jamin sekarang kami akan berada bersama kalian ..menangis bersama, Dan entahlah, melepas rindu.. namun sayangnya hal itu sedikit mustahil. Kami berdo'a dari sini untuk kesuksesan, kebahagiaan dan kehidupan kalian dihari esok dan seterusnya.. jaga diri baik2 kawan, maafkan kami sekali lagi yang tidak punya cukup uang untuk membeli tiket pesawat. Terimakasih karena telah menjadi bagian dari kehidupan kami, Terimakasih karena telah mewujudkan impian kami, Terimakasih karena telah meramaikan hidup kami.. we love you guys, sampai berjumpa lagi.. sungguh hal yang tak akan pernah patut untuk disesali, tinggal bersama kalian di rumah kami semua, Ma'had Darul Arqam #tapantri1830 #allaboutus

caption.text: I remember, my father used to say to me like this : "it is good if you could give yourself a rest sometimes, just one day, don't think about anything.. just remember all the goods that God has given you through everything. Remember the kindnesses that every single person you've met has given you throughout your life..just remember, what could have you been if not because of all those things? Then, remember, have you thanked them enough? Have you even just simply said 'thanks'? If no, please do so.. " and I did, Friday 05/17/13 was my very last day of High School in America, so I came to school in the morning and started to thank everybody. All my friends who has been amazingly nice and open to a complete stranger like me, all my teachers who has been incredibly kind and patient in teaching me, helping me, and everything that a stranger could ever wish for. my school staff including my counselor, administrator and lunch crew who has been outstandingly care and guided me whenever I got lost about anything.. and, just simply every-single-person I met throughout my exchange year in High Point High School. I'm so glad that I could thanked them, hugged them, and tell them how much I'm grateful to met them this year and that I'm leaving pretty soon.. THANK YOU so very much to all of you, that has been extremely awesomely very nice to me, to a complete stranger whom all of the sudden came into your life out of nowhere, but you guys treated me like I've been here forever.. may God bless every single one of you and, I love you. I wont never even dare to forget a single thing of your kindnesses, let me tell my grandchildren in time later that, once, I got to meet an amazing amazing people like you all in America.. :) #america #highpoinths #exchangeyear#lastday#onemonthtogo#thankyou#everybody :D :D

Well, to throw out my sadness today.. today was my LAST b-day at my school, so I brought my Indonesian souvenirs to give to all my friends as a remembrance of me. And everybody was giving me a so-called 'good bye hug', making me sooooooo sad that resulted in my flowing tears by the end of the day.. omg, I love you guys all so badly much, and this painting is from my bestiest Edward, and he said : "if I don't get to see you again, I hope you remember me." *silent* oh dear, may God bless all of them. Amin

Another thing to be grateful of. I am not an artist, even I cannot draw a sticky person figure rightly (lol!). So, this was my 2nd project in my sculpture class and I decided to drew a 'puppet shadow' (wayang) figure as my relief subject matter to represents Indonesian culture. Short story, Mr.Neal submitted it to an art exhibit by AP art students in my school, and after the show, all art submissions were judged by people from the Univ. Of Maryland department of art, and guess what?! Look what u found yesterday on the art school showcase? MY ARTWORK!! I can't believe this is really happened. This honorable mention, I sincerely present for my lovely Indonesia :D so glad that i can at least introduce all people in my school who sees my art into one from hundreds of Indonesian culture : puppet shadow (wayang) <3 ~High Point HS Visual Art Showcase, spring 2013.

Shall I? So I believe that every exchange students in this country have receives theirs as well, what a lifetime sign of a wonderful turn of my life. I can't be thankful enough for such an honor to be an exchange student, both United States and Indonesia gives me an important life lesson : explore the world and don't be afraid, because the real world is ahead you not behind you! Thanks Allah SWT and also for every single person in my life that helped me with this accomplishment, my new journey has just begun :D<3 the Unites States of America, May 2013.

Jadi keinget, dulu kalau bulan ramadhan paling seneng maen PS 'harvest moon' sama teh @muthiaghni sama a angga, Bisa2 ngabisin waktu seharian. Dulu selalu kepikiran kayaknya kehidupan dalem game itu asik banget : ada spring, fall, winter and summer. Ada bunga, buah, daun2, salju, dan pantai. Juga selalu kepengen ngerasain hidup kayak gitu : 4 musim. Well, Allah itu maha pemberi kasih.. siapa yang tau mimpi terkonyol yang berawal dari sumber Yang konyol ternyata bisa jadi kenyataan?? Siapa yang tau, bahwa Allah selalu mendengar permintaan2 kita sekonyol apapun itu, siapa yang tau? It's just about the matter of time. 
If you want something, pray for it. Ask for it. Then try to get it :D
Bermimpilah karena Tuhan senantiasa memeluk mimpi2 kita sekecil apapun itu :)
So, well, ya sekarang saya tau bagaimana itu summer, bagaimana itu autumn, bagaimana itu winter, dan akan merasakan bagaimana itu spring. Insya Allah. Amin.

caption.text:
Buat ayah tersayang :)
Ayah terbaik sedunia, ayah tersabar sepanjang masa, ayah tersholeh sejagad raya, ayah tersegala galanya tanpa ada batasan.
Makasih banyak buat segala galanya, buat hidup selama 17 tahun ini, buat segala doa ayah yang berhasil nganterin ade ke negri amerika ini. Makasih karena selalu jadi perunjuk dikala kehidupan terasa buntu, menjadi penghibur dikala nafas terasa sesak.
Makasih karena udah jagain ibu, ade, de zahra, sama de falah dengan sangan baik, memberi kami pemdidikan juga perlindungan teraman. 
Ayah, ade cuman pengen bikin ayah bangga, maaf kalau masih belum bisa terealisasiin semaksimal mungkin. Tapi ini, segala hal yang ade lakuin disini, di amerika, semuanya atas nama Allah, ibu dan ayah.
Ade sayang ayah, selamat ulang tahun yah. 
Semoga Allah menyayangi ayah sebagaimana ayah menyayangi ade selama ini. 
Amin.
